description:
Amazing pair of nude Yves Saint Laurent pumps, made in Italy. Red innersole,which the house used a lot in older designs before Louboutin tried to make it their go-to. Pre-worn, but in great condition, they could definitely be your new 'on the go' shoe. Complete with a 3" leather textured angled heel 9 3/4" insole length, these are the creme de la creme of comfort and classic.

Gives us "dia de la muertos" vibes. Straight from the archives, they don't make 'em as cute as this anymore.

description:
Super cute cranberry-colored suede mini bag, inspired by Chanel. The  geometrically-quilted  bag is 7 inches long, and 5 inches wide with great details. Several gold studs, a suede tassle, and a woven chain complete the bag making it a standout piece from the archives.

"Keep it simple, keep it minimal, keep it mini."

name: SWRV M$ Sticker Nº1: Clair Huxtable
description: The first sticker of many in our new sticker series M$ was inspired by our recent lookbook by the same name . Nº1 in the series is Clair Huxtable: the G.O.A.T of M$. Smart, beautiful, confident, witty, strong, knowledgeable, individualistic with exquisite style; Clair represents the crème de la crème of throwback styles for SWRV when it comes to women in American TV. These stickers will come free with SWRV Women's orders. 1 buck for everyone else. 1, 3inch Vinyl Sticker with graphic image of Clair and text that reads: Don't You Dare Open Your Mouth When I Ask You A Question. Big ups to you if you know what episode that line is taken from.

name: '86 Kenneth J. Lane Drop Jewels Necklace
description:
A vintage necklace that looks like it came straight out of sunken treasure, this piece is a dream. Large geometric gemstones blend beautifully with the gold tone chain for a once-in-a-lifetime piece that will surely turn heads.  The muliti-colored cabochons have a textured back that give them depth. Bright gold tone finish. This style is named: "Caprianti". Marked on an oval cartouche: "K.J.L. for AVON", signifying that it was created by jewelery designer Kenneth J. Lane for Avon, a creative partnership that lasted from the 1980s-1990s. This is one of the most famous pieces from that partnership. Necklace measures 19 inches long.  Don't sleep on this one!

<iframe width="200" height="180" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/OD6Yq2r28dk" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>

name: Bloomingdale's Little Pink Bag
description:
Bloomingdale's is an iconic American department store started in NYC on 938 Third Avenue in 1872. We've all heard of Bloomingdale's 'Little Brown Bag', and now SWRV wants you to meet it's cute, high maintenance cousin. This Little Pink Bag is a bucket style, quilted in vibrant pink leather and comes from the early 1990s era of the Bloomingdale's brand collection. The classic black and gold embroidered Bloomingdale's tag is stitched on the inside of the bag. The Little Pink Bag measures 6 inches tall, and 8 inches wide with a pink leather strap and gold magnetic snap closure. This little bag is a big way to show you know what's up.

<iframe width="200" height="143" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/uTZX8hEjftY" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>

name: PIERRE CARDIN by Pierre Cardin Aftershave Lotion
description:
Keep your cuts fresh as ever with this classic Pierre Cardin brand aftershave lotion with the famous Pierre Cardin fragrance. Launched by the design house of Pierre Cardin in 1972, PIERRE CARDIN is classified as a refreshing, subtle, oriental fragrance. This masculine scent possesses a blend of fresh and spicy, a scent that lingers, very male. It is recommended for romantic wear.  This deadstock 4oz. aftershave comes in a very special branded box and bottle. If you need any further motivation, just know that a woman is writing this description and yes guys, this-is-a-winner. Comes brand new in the box, unopened.  Grab it while it lasts.

<iframe width="200" height="180" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/ThqnzVymIPg" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>

name: '88 Liz Claiborne Woven Technicolor Purse
description:
This is a more than amazing Liz Claiborne classic bursting with color and ready to take on the heat. Made in Italy, it is in excellent condition, and trust us when we say, they don't make em' like this anymore. This bag is 8 inches tall, and 11 inches wide with a braided red cord strap and magnetic snap closure. Red is used through out the bag, as Liz Claiborne loved the color so much, her creative team dubbed it "Liz Red".  Liz Claiborne was a staple amongst fashionable, independent women throughout the 1980's and 90s with her company Liz Claiborne Inc. becoming the first company founded by a woman to ever become a Fortune 500. Her bold designs still ring true for women of today.

<iframe width="200" height="143" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/Fto_YTViRr0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>

name: '03 NYC Blackout Tee
description:
AKA "The Big Blackout". If you were in NYC in 2003, you will definitely remember this monumental blackout and how it shut everything down. And if you weren't, you're in for a good story. One superhot day in August, just before sun down,  trains, elevators, lights and all shut down across the entire Big Apple due to an oversurge of energy. Millions of people crossed the Brooklyn Bridge in the dark, danced in Union Square in the dark and flooded the streets in panic and amazement. While people couldn't turn on their tvs (and didn't have Twitter) they did what was natural...came together to watch the stars in the sky. This tee is a great way to commemorate the natural phenomenon that happened that day.

<iframe width="200" height="180" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/6nt0njgVmv4" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>

name: Diadora Snapback
description: Since 1948 Diadora has been the only Italian athletic footwear and apparel manufacturer to produce their products in Italy. Founder Marcello Daniel, along with his wife’s help, lifted the company off the ground in 1948, and in 1950, the two launched their first product which were their mountain climbing boots. Since the 1950’s Diadora has never stopped creating their best of products out of Italy. To celebrate a part of Marcello’s Diadora legacy SWRV will be offering deadstock Diadora snapbacks. The hats are made of 100% nylon. Italian snapbacks: a really clean way to bring the outfit together.

name: Diadora Racer Hat
description: Since 1948 Diadora has been the only Italian athletic footwear and apparel manufacturer to produce their products in Italy. Founder Marcello Daniel, along with his wife’s help, lifted the company off the ground in 1948, and in 1950, the two launched their first product which were their mountain climbing boots. Since the 1950’s Diadora has never stopped creating their best of products out of Italy. To celebrate a part of Marcello’s Diadora legacy SWRV will be offering classic Diadora racer hats. Perfect for sunny days on your bike. Details Hat is white with pink embroidered logo and baby blue accents. Racer style with elastic back.

name: Starter™ Green Bay Packers 1997 Championship Snapback
description:
The Green Bay Packers Championship Starter snap back is the reflection of Super Bowl 31 when the Green Bay Packers punished Drew Bledsoe and the New England Patriots 35 to 21. This piece holds the history of treasured moments like when Desmond Howard sets the tone right off the back for Green Bay with an awesome 32 yard kick return setting up the legendary Brett Farve to score the first touchdown of the game on their 2nd play passing a 54 yard pass to Andre Rising. This Starter snap back is amazing commorating one of Green Bay Packer’s most enthusiastic games of all time. Get it while it lasts!

<U><small><B>Details</u>
Snap back strap is black.</small> Hat is deadstock Starter™ with tags.

Reebok created there own basketball movement with “Black Top” that considered no fouls and no rules. If your on the “Black Top” your playing street ball. Lil Shorty and Sinbad know what the “Black Top” is all about. You might want to cop this all over print tee in a hurry, next time you check for this it might be ghost! SEE YA!

name: Georgetown University Bull Dog Basketball Tee
description:
This allover print “Georgetown University Bull dog Tee” brings back so many good memories with one of the best basketball players to ever play the game: Allen Iverson. With Allen Iverson’s quick cross overs, mind blowing assists, defense, and points per game no one would dear take their eyes off of this kid when the ball was in his hands. Allen Iverson’s was a phenomenal player at G-town. Ai’s first season playing basketball for Georgetown he was honored “Big East Rookie -of -the –year” also “Big East defensive player -of -the –year”. As a sophomore in college Allen Iverson dominated so bad in the games he made an opportunity available for himself to enter the NBA draft of 1996 , from there the rest is history. Georgetown University will always be known as the first home of Allen Iverson’s historical college records from 94’ to 96’ and they all live inside this t-shirt.

name: '97 Nike™ x Bob Marley x Micheal Jordan Jammin' Tee

"Jammin" is a song by the reggae band  Bob Marley & the Wailers from their 1977 album “Exodus”. 10 years later the song “Jamming” was re-released as a tribute to Bob Marley and was instantly a re-born hit, as in the Netherlands where it was classified on the chart for 4 weeks straight. In 1997, Nike released a special edition Bob Marley's We're Jammin' t-shirt to commemorate the 30th anniversary of the the collaborated hit between Bob Marley & The Wailers. In 2011 (fourteen years later) SWRV is presenting the classic vintage gem “We’re Jammin”, “We’re Jammin” T-shirt. Nike Grey Tag era. This tee will not be available for long. Act fast!

name: Cross ⊗ Colours  Denim
description: These are a great pair of Cross Colours jeans in their most famous colorway : golden yellow denim and with a green stitch. The Cross Colours brand wasn't merely selling clothing, it was pushing a message: "Clothing Without Prejudice." That slogan appeared on every garment. Since the brand was primarily targeting African-American youth, they wanted to inspire them with positive messages like “Stop D Violence” and “Educate 2 Elevate”. Cross Colours clothing wasn't just a fashion statement, they represented a political and social message we believe heavily in at SWRVBIZ. Add to cart + spread the word.

name: Levi's Button Your Shorts Tee
description: Here is a 1991 Levi's "Button Your Shorts" tee, from the 90's "Button Your Fly" campaign. You can catch all your favorite childhood super stars sporting this shirt from Zack Morris On Save By The Bell all the way to Left Eye from TLC on the What About Your Friends? music video. What else can i say about this piece? It's definitely one of Levi's most memorable. Say wussup to summer fun.

name: Beat Soup Volume 3
description: (60min mix) of the Beat Soup mix CD series by Ras G [Poohbah Records] This is the music that people will be playing in the ghettos of Mars in the year 3014. Ras G guides a deep space exploration of music’s ancient history and rich future. Ras G has been a fixture on the underground hiphop scene in Los Angeles since the early 90s. His music is rich with space-funktified rhythms, fog horns, natty chattin, subterranean bass lines, colossal percussion and glorious highs. His latest, Beat Soup Volume 3 brings names like Frank Zappa, Ghostface Killah, Oddfuture, Hudson Mowhawke, Klipmode and Flying Lotus together all in one 60 minute adventure - and that's not even half the mix. Get them while supplies last [on this planet].

name: Adidas AZOOM Sky Diving League Shirt
description:
Fly high with this Adidas team classic. Circa 1998, this quarter-buttoned shirt was the second-generation of a variety of special team shirts that had been dropped starting the mid-1980s.
The shirt body is a cotton-blend with a collar detail and inside lining. This design keeps it interesting with blue and fuchsia pinstripes with the 'Calamity Cliffs' team graphic on the left half of the shirt. The back has an amazing graphic that commemorates the 1998 Sky Diving championship held in Mexico. Definitely meant to be worn by only the the flyest.

An 80's Dogtown-era multi-colored terrycloth sweatshirt with the message California Dreaming spanning 15" front and back. A stunning piece to layer.

description: 20th Anniversary commemorative Polo cotton sweatshirt with red/yellow/cobalt/white colorway. Embroidered crest reads the years 1967-1987. A piece of Polo history.

name: Ralph Lauren Polo Sport Pullover
description: Discontinued vintage Polo Sport 100% Cotton quarter-zipper pullover. Kelly Green color. Bold embroidered Polo Sport logo © 1996. A definite score for your Spring Polo collection.

name: Ralph Lauren Polo CPRL '93 Canvas Backpack
description:
This bag is beyond the norm. Circa 1993, this incredible canvas bag has an rich all-over Americana nautical theme. The American Flag and sailboats cover the front and back of the canvas with leather and twill cotton accents and zipper enclosure found on the back of bag with a bold CPRL 93. 18" wide x 17" tall - 7" gusset.  A rare impressive Lo piece.

<small> Details- Very minor natural wear on flag. </small>

name: Polo Sport Rugby © '96
description: The classic Polo Sport rugby in high quality. This bi-color rugby is a rare dig with the large POLO SPORT embroidery found right in the center. Definitely a stand-out piece for the above-average Polo collector.

name: Ralph Lauren Polo Sportsman Pullover
description: Blazing hot red Ralph Lauren piece from the Polo Sportsman Line circa mid 90s with killer details. A quarter-button enclosure fleece pullover with nylon patches on the elbow offers a dope color contrast. The collar is a rich corduroy, with the Sportsman logo patch found on the left arm. Drawstring-bottom gives you complete style control. An essential & clever Polo piece.

name: Kimono Bloom Blouse
description: This sheer black Kimono Bloom Blouse touts glamorous draping sleeves, a traditional neckline paired with a stunning multi-color floral pattern [Cherry/Blue/Gold/Fuchsia] and simple button-enclosures. The blouse works excellent paired with high-waisted skirts or pants.

name: Gianni Versace V2 by Versace Sweater
description: This is an luscious piece from the late-great Gianni Versace V2 Collection. Impressive circular designs full of color [blue, orange, green & yellow] in 100% Cotton, Made In Italy. The V2 by Versace collection was a joint venture originally between Ermenegildo Zegna and designer Gianni Versace in the 1990’s. Perfect piece to add taking your outfit from an 8 to a 10. In brand-new/immaculate condition.

name: Gianni Versace Jeans Couture
description:
Another remarkable Item from the late,great Gianni Versace. Pastel Yellow Gianni Versace, Versace Jeans Couture Piece. Buttery soft 100% cotton. 
Measurements are 41" in length 14" across waist and  31" inseam. A Beautiful piece to dress up or down this spring.

name: MCM Monogram Snapback
description: MCM archival snapback hat in white/black monogram. This deadstock hat is © 80s. This is a very popular hat that spawned from the 80s designer-label craze. MCM is an amazing luxury brand that stands alone with their unique leather-goods, such as luggage, handbags, briefcases, and other accessories.

name: MCM Hiking Boots
description: Simply Amazing ! A very rare Deadstock pair of blue and brown two tone Vintage MCM boots. Gold MCM logo plaque on the side. Delicious detailing on the back and side heel of the boot. Great for any terrain. Most definitely a one of kind piece. The renowned European luxury brand MCM is making a major come back in the premium accessories market. Drawing inspiration from decades-old heritage, the company specializes in manufacturing superior quality leather travel goods, as well as stylish and functional pieces such as handbags, small leather goods, luggage and clothing.

name: MCM Passport Pouch
description: Another impressive piece from MCM . An archival Visetos pouch that can be worn around the neck or body. Style meets utility, as the bag is great for inner-city travel to fit your Metrocards or PASMOs, iPODS or YSL gloss. The possibilities are endless. Available in cognac or white monogram.

name: Ellesse Adjustable Hat
description:
Classic Ellesse adjustable pull-tab cap in a lush navy blue circa the mid-80s.
100% Cotton with vibrant Ellesse logo in red/orange embroidered.The Ellesse logo references the form of a tennis ball with the shape of the tips of a pair of skis.

Through the 1970s and 1980s, Ellesse gained a reputation for combining sportswear functionality with street-level fashion styling. It was one of the first sportswear brands to feature their logo prominently on the outside of its garments. Celebrities associated with the brand include boxer Muhammad Ali and actors Brigitte Nielsen and Roger Moore.

 During the mid-1980s, French designer Jean-Charles de Castelbajac worked with Ellesse, an early collaboration between a sportswear company and a fashion designer.
